items.title: Jesse Wilson Sam Berlin This is why I said don't do wildcards in Guice! code: binder.bind(key) .t...

object.content:
Jesse Wilson Sam Berlin This is why I said don't do wildcards in Guice!

code:
binder.bind(key)
.toProvider(new Provider<JsonConverter>() {
@Inject Injector injector;
@Inject JsonConverter.Builder builder;

@Override public JsonConverter get() {
Map<Type, Converter<?, ?>> converters = injector.getInstance(
key.ofType(new TypeLiteral<Map<Type, Converter<?, ?>>>() {}));
for (Map.Entry<Type, Converter<?, ?>> entry : converters.entrySet()) {
builder.register(entry.getKey(), entry.getValue());
}
return builder.build();
}
})
.in(Scopes.SINGLETON);

object.content:
"Yet today, with the recent introduction of the Gcard, bills can now go directly to Google... So, in true Google spirit and values, this is your friendly, if somewhat serious reminder, that all of us have an obligation to continue to treat Google’s money as if it were our own."

Im not sure he knows what he's asking for. If I had $50 billion in the bank, I'd be buying islands on a whim, not being "responsible" with my Gcard.

items.title: Browserchannel using jQuery (including RPC multiplexing): $.ajax({ type: 'POST', url: '/async', d...

object.content:
Browserchannel using jQuery (including RPC multiplexing):

$.ajax({
type: 'POST',
url: '/async',
dataType: 'json',
data: args,
success: function(dataList) {
for (var i = 0; i < dataList.length; i++) {
//Dispatch result based on action name.
var data = dataList[i];
self.callbacks_[data.rpc].call(this, data);
}

// If we drop to having zero connected channels, then connect a new one.
self.activeChannels_--;
if (self.activeChannels_ == 0) {
self.connect(); // recursive call
}
},
failure: function() {
alert("Failed to contact server =(");
self.activeChannels_--;
}
});
